    <h2 class="display-lg">Copy-paste is broken for AI workflows.</h2>

    <div class="body-text mt-6">
      <p>
        You're trying to ask Claude about a ticket in your team's tracker. Or a doc in your internal wiki. Or a row in your admin panel. The page lives behind your login — no vendor CLI reaches it, no third-party export covers it.
      </p>
      <p>
        Copy-paste sort of works, until it doesn't: tables turn to text soup, code blocks lose their fences, nested lists flatten, and the link back to the source disappears.
      </p>
      <p>
        trakdown runs <em>in your browser, as you</em>. Same session, same cookies, same authenticated page — turned into clean markdown in one keystroke.
      </p>
